-- Erste Group says no contact from U.S. authorities
-- By Michael Shields
-- Tue Jul 08, 2014 06:14AM EDT
-- None



VIENNA, July 8 (Reuters) - Austria's Erste Group Bank <ERST.VI> is not in touch with U.S. officials who have been probing European banks about dealings with countries blacklisted by the United States, a bank spokesman said on Tuesday.

"We have not been contacted by U.S. authorities," a spokesman for Austria's biggest bank said. Its shares were down 3.4 percent at 18.325 euros by 1013 GMT in a weaker European bank sector <.SX7P>. U.S. authorities have begun settlement talks with Germany's Commerzbank and Deutsche Bank over their dealings with blacklisted countries, a source with knowledge of the investigation said earlier.  Deutsche Bank <DBKGn.DE> and Commerzbank <CBKG.DE> declined to comment. [ID:nL4N0PJ28K]